# ── API base ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Leave blank (or omit) — the code falls back to '' which makes fetch() use
# a RELATIVE path (/api/upload). This works on:
#   • Vite dev server  → the proxy in vite.config.js forwards /api → localhost:3001
#   • Vercel production → /api/* routes are resolved by Vercel’s serverless functions
# Setting this to http://localhost:3001 BREAKS production because Vite bakes the
# value into the bundle at build time, so every Vercel request hits localhost.
VITE_API_BASE=
